div.p:
Ay, the heads of the
maids, or their
maidenheads;

Adding to clouds more
clouds with his deep
sighs;

Through lovers' brains,
and then they dream of
love;

He heareth not, he
stirreth not, he moveth
not;

With love's light wings
did I o'er-perch these
walls;

For this, being smelt,
with that part cheers each
part;

Good king of cats, nothing
but one of your nine
lives;
